        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 3 at 5:58AM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>Light snow has developed in the Bozeman Valley and it extends east
to Bozeman Pass. This snow should start to decrease after 8 am.

Minor accumulations of less than one inch are expected at the
Bozeman Yellowstone Airport, up to 2 inches in the city of
Bozeman, and 2 to 4 inches at Bozeman Pass and in surrounding
mountains.

Please drive carefully around the area this morning. Roads will be
slick, likely with slushy snow accumulation. Allow extra time to
reach your destination this morning.
</description>
